    "function": "Mediates the voltage-dependent sodium ion permeability of excitable membranes. Assuming opened or closed conformations in response to the voltage difference across the membrane, the protein forms a sodium-selective channel through which Na(+) ions may pass in accordance with their electrochemical gradient (PubMed:10827969, PubMed:11166117, PubMed:28137877). Implicated in the regulation of hippocampal replay occurring within sharp wave ripples (SPW-R) important for memory (PubMed:29867081)",
